item.title: Pannun files civil lawsuit in US against GOI, Doval and others, seeks damages
item.description: Gurpatwant Singh Pannun of Sikhs for Justice has filed a civil lawsuit against the Indian government and key officials in a US court. He seeks compensation for an alleged assassination attempt on him last year. The plot, involving high-ranking Indian officials, was foiled by undercover US agents. Pannun claims ongoing threats to his life.
item.dc:creator: NAOMI CANTON

item.title: Sean Diddy says he won't bring women home in his fresh bail plea
item.description: Sean Diddy has submitted a fresh bail plea after his initial request was denied. Facing charges of racketeering, sex trafficking, and transportation for prostitution, he promises not to allow women into his Florida mansion. Arrested after multiple allegations of sexual abuse during 'freak off' sessions, Diddy has not pleaded guilty and claims innocence.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US intensifies criticism of Pak ballistic missile programme
item.description: The United States reaffirms its long-standing opposition to supporting Pakistan's ballistic missile program, emphasizing continued enforcement of sanctions for national security. Recent US sanctions targeted a Chinese research institute and companies for allegedly supplying missile-related items to Pakistan. In response, Pakistan criticized the actions as biased and politically motivated.
item.dc:creator: Omer Farooq Khan

item.title: Kimberly Guilfoyle now shares a kissing photo with Donald Trump Jr amid Bettina Anderson row
item.description: ​"I would love to see you in the White House Kimberly. The Trump family will never find another loyal and dedicated individual as yourself...." a follower wrote to Kimberly's Instagram post in which she was seen with Donald Trump Jr at an event during the weekends. The photos come amid speculations of tension in their relationship because pf Don Jr's apparent proximity with Bettina Anderson.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Tesla, SpaceX, X employees donate more to Kamala Harris, despite Musk's support for Trump
item.description: Elon Musk endorses Donald Trump for the upcoming US presidential election, contrasting with his employees at Tesla, SpaceX, and X who support Kamala Harris. OpenSecrets data reveals significant donations from employees to Harris's campaign. Previously a supporter of Joe Biden in 2020, Musk has now shifted his political stance to the right.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: At least two killed in gas field explosion in Uzbekistan
item.description: An explosion at an under-construction gas field in Uzbekistan killed at least two people and injured others. Occurring near Baysun, this follows a previous incident releasing hydrogen sulphide gas. Authorities closed schools and evacuated workers. Discovered during the Soviet era, the gas field is now being developed with foreign investment.

item.title: Does Barron Trump really have 4 crypto wallets? Why it matters
item.description: ​“Barron knows so much about this, Barron’s a young guy, but he knows. He talks about his wallet, he’s got four wallets or something, and I’ll say ‘what is a wallet?’” Donald Trump said at the launch of the World Liberty Financial -- the crypto project of the Trumps. 18-year-old Barron is the DeFi visionary of this project and as claimed by his father, Barron has exceptional understanding about crypto.

item.title: Explosives found near Donald Trump's rally site at Long Island? Cops say 'no threat'
item.description: After two assassination attempts on former president Donald Trump, explosives were reportedly found in a car near the site where Donald Trump is scheduled to address a rally at Long Island. Nassau County Police department confirmed that there was a suspicious occurrence on Wednesday ahead of Trump's address but there was no threat to the Republican presidential candidate.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Melania Trump says she's proud of her nude modeling work: 'Are we no longer...?'
item.description: Melania Trump said more that her nude modeling works the media scrutiny on her past profession is a graver concern. In a teaser video of her upcoming memoir, she addressed the concern that became a bothering question during the 2016 election campaign -- to-be first lady's nude shoots. As Trump runs for reelection and his fashion model wife emerges as a writer, Melania answers the question.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump claims 'fantastic' Modi is coming to US to meet him
item.description: Donald Trump claimed that Prime Minister Narendra Modi will visit the US to meet him next week. PM Modi's official schedule includes attending the Quad summit hosted by President Biden and other events in New York City, but no meeting with Trump is listed. The Indian Embassy and State Department have not commented on Trump's claim.
item.dc:creator: Chidanand Rajghatta

item.title: What is a walkie-talkie? Device linked to round 2 of fatal explosions in Lebanon
item.description: On Wednesday, explosions linked to walkie-talkies used by Hezbollah struck Lebanon's southern regions and Beirut's suburbs, causing numerous casualties and injuries. Thousands of explosive-rigged pagers detonated simultaneously. In response, Hezbollah launched rocket strikes on Israeli artillery positions, escalating tensions in the region.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Donald Trump, Melania's photo with little Tiffany Trump viral. Reason is...
item.description: The Trump campaign shared an old family photo featuring Donald, Melania, and Tiffany Trump to showcase their familial side. Tiffany Trump, daughter from Donald's marriage to Marla Maples, usually stays out of the spotlight but supports her father's campaigns. Donald Trump Jr, Eric Trump, Barron Trump are part of the Trump campaign while Ivanka Trump was his advisor in the previous stint.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Japan: 'Jealous' husband arrested after making over 100 nuisance calls every day for a month
item.description: A Japanese man harassed his wife with 100 silent calls daily for a month due to jealousy. The woman from Hyogo prefecture reported it to the police after suspecting her husband's involvement. Police confirmed he was behind the calls, leading to his arrest. This incident has sparked discussions on relationship communication and controlling behavior.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump megadonor, billionaire says he would pull his money from market if Harris wins
item.description: John Paulson, a major Trump fundraiser and hedge fund billionaire, said he would withdraw his investments if Kamala Harris wins the presidential election. He cites concerns over her proposed economic policies, including higher taxes on corporate profits and unrealized gains. ​“I’d go into cash and I’d go into gold because I think the uncertainty regarding the plans they outlined would create a lot of uncertainty in the markets and likely lower markets," John Paulson said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Gavin Newsom targets AI deepfakes with new law: Why Elon Musk and others think it's a really bad idea
item.description: California Governor Gavin Newsom signed bills banning political deepfakes and misleading AI-generated content. The laws mandate disclosures in political ads, require online platforms to remove deceptive content within 72 hours, and penalize creators of false information about candidates. These measures will help to combat the harmful use of deepfakes in political ads and other content.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Pakistan high court halts verdict in Imran Khan, Bushra Bibi corruption case
item.description: The Islamabad High Court has restrained a trial court from issuing its verdict in the Al-Qadir Trust corruption case involving former Prime Minister Imran Khan and his wife, Bushra Bibi. They petitioned for acquittal, citing recent amendments in anti-corruption laws that they argue invalidate the charges. The trial remains ongoing with notices issued to involved parties.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala Harris-hater Laura Loomer says she's not loyal to Republican Party
item.description: Far-right activist Laura Loomer said she is not loyal to either of the political parties -- the Republican and the Democratic Party. Her loyalty lies only to former president Donald Trump and many Republicans have a problem with that, she said. GOP presidential candidate Donald Trump, VP candidate JD Vance did not endorse Laura Loomer's curry comment but also emphasized that she is not part of Trump campaign.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Train cancelled in Britain after squirrel refuses to disembark
item.description: A British train was cancelled after two squirrels boarded and one refused to disembark. The incident disrupted the 08:54 Reading to Gatwick Airport service, forcing it to terminate early at Redhill. Despite staff efforts, one squirrel remained on board, resulting in the service's premature end.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
